# 2-Cents Posts

## Emojis

Maximize related emojis in every post. Use them in:

- Section headings (e.g. `🏗️ A structure that scales`)
- Lead paragraphs and list items where they reinforce meaning
- Homepage card titles / tags when natural

Prefer topic-relevant emojis over generic ones. Do not sprinkle them randomly — each emoji should map to the idea next to it.

## Article pages sidebar

On every `two-cents/*.html` page, the left nav must include:

1. **Home** → `../index.html`
2. **2-Cents** → `../index.html#two-cents`
3. **Nested article list** under 2-Cents with every available post

When adding a new post, update the nested article list on **all** existing post pages so readers can jump between articles without returning home.

Mark the current article with `class="active"` on its `<li>`.

On every article page, the breadcrumbs header should use the cents emoji:

```html
<section id="breadcrumbs" class="breadcrumbs">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="d-flex justify-content-between align-items-center">
      <h2>🪙 2-Cents</h2>
      …
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
```

Do **not** put the cents emoji in the left sidebar nav label.

```html
<nav class="nav-menu">
  <ul>
    <li><a href="../index.html"><i class="bx bx-home"></i> <span>Home</span></a></li>
    <li class="nav-two-cents">
      <a href="../index.html#two-cents"><i class="bx bx-bulb"></i> <span>2-Cents</span></a>
      <ul class="nav-two-cents-articles">
        <li class="active"><a href="building-an-org-monorepo.html">🏗️ Building an Org Monorepo</a></li>
        <!-- add new articles here -->
      </ul>
    </li>
  </ul>
</nav>
```
